The US government has rolled out a Sh200 million regional peace initiative ahead of Kenya&rsquo;s general election next August 8.This is part of a bigger programme to be launched at an estimated cost of Sh3 billion, which will cover the whole country.The regional programme called Kenya Election Violence Prevention will be carried out in Kisumu, Nandi and Nakuru. US Ambassador Robert Godec said the programme brings together government officials, security agencies, the IEBC, businesspeople, civil society, political and religious leaders. The aim is to ensure peace during the elections. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s only by Kenyans joining hands and standing together that they will make certain the election will be successful,&rdquo; he said. Godec spoke during the launch in Kisumu on Thursday.The programme is being carried out by Mercy Corps and others.